				<h2><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20111121233516/http://www.worldstallestwatersphere.com/?p=320" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Site Styling – New Width">Site Styling &#8211; New Width</a></h2>
				<small>April 24th, 2011 <!-- by Spheroid --></small>
				
				<div class="entry">
					<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20111121233516/http://www.worldstallestwatersphere.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/NookWTWS640.jpg"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20111121233516im_/http://www.worldstallestwatersphere.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/NookWTWS640-213x320.jpg" alt="" title="Nook WTWS 640" width="213" height="320" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-321"/></a>The World&#8217;s Tallest Water Sphere has had some site formatting updates. The site now has a default width of 960 over the older, narrower 760 pixels. The site has been validated with several mobile and tablet devices, such as the Nook shown here.</p>
<p>Let us know if your device or browser has trouble reading the site, and we will fix it.<br/>
<br clear="right"/></p>
