				<h2><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20111121233516/http://www.worldstallestwatersphere.com/?p=308" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Wallops Island, Virginia">Wallops Island, Virginia</a></h2>
				<small>March 6th, 2011 <!-- by Spheroid --></small>
				
				<div class="entry">
					<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20111121233516/http://www.worldstallestwatersphere.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/WallopsIslandWaterTower480.jpg"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20111121233516im_/http://www.worldstallestwatersphere.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/WallopsIslandWaterTower4801-213x320.jpg" alt="WallopsIslandWaterTowerThumnail" title="WallopsIslandWaterTowerThumnail" width="213" height="320" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-310"/></a>This photo of a glorious water tower is sent in via reader Jason Dengel. The water tower was completed on Wallops Island, Virginia in July of 2010. It stands 287 feet tall and holds 200,000. The water tank is used to service the nearby NASA launch pads.</p>
<p>Nice view of the tower, the construction equipment, and the backing Atlantic Ocean. Thanks Jason!<br/>
<br clear="left"/></p>
				</div>
		
